# Infrastructure layer

Path: `app/Infrastructure/{BC}/{Model|Repository|ReadModel|Mapper|Listener|Service}`.

Shared tech adapters: `app/Infrastructure/Shared/...` (event publisher, etc.).

Naming: English only. No Russian. No transliteration.

## Allowed

- Eloquent `Model` ‚Äî persistence only, no domain invariants
- `Repository` ‚Äî implements `App\Domain\{same BC}\Repository\*`
- `ReadModel` ‚Äî implements `App\Application\{same BC}\ReadPort\*`
- `Mapper` ‚Äî Model ‚Üî Aggregate (via Domain `reconstitute`) and Model ‚Üí Application DTO
- `Listener` ‚Äî reacts to **other BC** domain events, runs **own** BC command handlers
- `Service` ‚Äî technical adapters only (files, external APIs, queues wiring)
- Depend on Domain / Application ports of the **same** BC + `App\Shared\...` + Laravel

## Forbidden

- Business invariants in Models / Repositories / Mappers
- Calling another BC‚Äôs Application handlers / repositories / ReadModels from Repository or Mapper
- Hydrating aggregates via reflection ‚Äî only Domain `reconstitute` (or equivalent explicit factory)
- Cross-BC Eloquent relations as domain coupling (IDs only)
- HTTP / controllers here (Interface layer)

## Cross-BC mutations

Only via domain events.

Flow: own handler saves aggregate ‚Üí `DomainEventPublisher` ‚Üí **sync** listener in target BC ‚Üí target BC command handler.

```php
// ‚ùå BAD ‚Äî Order infra opens Workshop handler directly inside repository
$this->openProductionTaskHandler->handle(...);

// ‚úÖ GOOD ‚Äî publish events; Workshop Listener reacts sync
$this->events->publish($order->pullDomainEvents());
// Infrastructure/Workshop/Listener/... ‚Üí OpenProductionTaskHandler
```

Pilot: listeners are **synchronous** (no `ShouldQueue` unless explicitly requested later).

## Structure

| Folder | Role |
|--------|------|
| `Model` | Eloquent models, casts, persistence relations |
| `Mapper` | toDomain / toPersistence / toDTO; uses Aggregate `reconstitute` |
| `Repository` | Write side adapters for Domain repositories |
| `ReadModel` | Read side adapters for Application ReadPorts |
| `Listener` | Sync event ‚Üí own BC command |
| `Service` | Non-domain technical services |

## DI

Bind ports in a dedicated provider (e.g. `PersistenceServiceProvider`): Domain Repository, Application ReadPort, `DomainEventPublisher`, event‚Üílistener map.
